They have an overseas territory known as "Hatsunian Micronesia" which consists of Mariana Island, Marshall Islands, and Caroline. Hatsunia purchased these from the Spanish in 1899 after their defeat in the Spanish-American War. Today they are a major tourist destination and the natives have equal rights as well.

by Karamiko » Tue Sep 08, 2020 11:13 pm

Lazarie is something quite unusual in the eastern wing of the Axis bloc - a Francophone island nation lumped in with the rest of the Japanese Empire's co-prosperity sphere. After Japan won World War II, and with it ownership over a vast sphere of influence in Asia and the Pacific, the critically overextended IJA was forced to withdraw, and grant autonomy to Lazarie and presumably other GEACPS territories. As a result, Lazarie's current geopolitical situation is a game of seeing how much independence they can get away with while a single IJA garrison is watching the islands.
